 M4 Ramps

 .750 Gas Block area


ALL NFA RULES APPLY 

The .223 Wylde hybrid chamber was designed by Bill Wylde of Greenup, IL to exploit the accuracy advantages of the .223 Remington chambering without pressure problems or compromising the functional reliability of (semi) automatic weapons like the AR-15 family when using 5.56×45mm NATO military ammunition.  Coincidentally, it shoots the relatively long and heavy 80-grain bullets commonly used in the sport of Highpower Rifle Competition very well and is one of the preferred chambers for that use. The Wylde chamber is used by a few rifle manufacturers who sell "National Match" configuration AR-15 rifles, barrels, and upper receivers.

title: For Sale:  romo ak 47.  not wsar
postcontent: The Romanian SAR series of rifles was imported in the late 1990s and early 2000s. Much like the MAK-90, they can take double stack mags, but do not have the threaded muzzle or bayonet lug. SARs had a US pistol grip, US piston, and US trigger group installed to make them 922r compliant. They come in three calibers, 7.62x39, 5.45x39, and 5.56x45 in the SAR1, SAR2, and SAR3 respectively. These rifles are generally well thought of, and are often good shooters. Fit and finish are often less than perfect as is common with Romanian guns, but that is only cosmetic. title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare REal Ghost Gun- Sites Spectre 9mm SMG
location: Tacoma, Olympia, Lacey, Shelton, Centralia, Southwest Washington, Washington
postcontent:
Its a ghost because of the name Spectre and its a phantom because its so rare. Made in Italy these were the Italian answer to the MP5. Very few made it into the US as the Semi Auto version known as HC or M4 Spectre.  Its very unique and well built/designed its hefty made of metal not plastic, metal receiver and metal bolt it really soaks up the recoil.  It has a quad stack 30 rd coffin style magazine. It has a decocker switch so you can cock, decock it, and then it will be in double action for the first shot, then single action after that. you can also leave it cocked and locked in single action like a regular fire arm. the double action allows the operater to be ready to shoot with the safety off but with a safe long double pull trigger 

I am only getting rid of it because i have some other guns i want to get. its a great collectable firearm thats been in a safe for over 10 years. round count is close to 100.  the last picture shown here is from Leon the Professional where he is handling the full auto version.
